Mechanical System.Name: Planet
Mechanical System.Notes:
The units chosen for this system are such that the Gravitational constant G is 1.
The units are:
- Mass: 1 mass_unit = 2 x 10^30 Kg (1 Solar mass)
- Length: 1 length_unit = 1.5 x 10^11 m (1 Astronomical Unit, the average distance between the Earth and the Sun)
- Time: 1 time_unit = 5 x 10^6 s (about 58 days)
In this unit: 
- the Earth mass is m = 0.00003 (1 Solar mass = 333,030 Earth masses)
- r is measured in Astronomical units (typical value around 1 for this simulation)
- drdt is measured in Astronomical Units/(58 days)
- theta is measured in radians
- dthetadt is measured in rad/(58 days) (the formula for the angular velocity is dthetadt = w = v/r, with v = sqrt(GM/r), so in these units v = 1/sqrt(r) 
  and w = 1/(r * sqrt(r), therefore if r is 1 AU, w is 1 AU/(58 days); if r is 2 AUs, then w is 1/(2 * sqrt(2)) = 0.353 AU/(58 days) )
